{
	"$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/refs/heads/dev/assets/oh-my-opencode.schema.json",
	// Model Mapping Reference: https://github.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/blob/dev/src/shared/model-requirements.ts
	"agents": {
		"sisyphus": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-7",
			"variant": "max",
			"fallback_models": [
				"opencode-go/kimi-k2.6",
				"opencode-go/glm-5",
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "medium"
				}
			]
		},
		"hephaestus": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
			"variant": "medium",
			"prompt_append": "# Hephaestus additional prompt\n\n## Autonomy\n\nUnless the user explicitly asks to be consulted for decisions, do not ask for decisions. Work autonomously using the available context, repository conventions, and reasonable assumptions.\n\n## Issue-fixing workflow\n\nFor issue-fixing tasks, create a pull request or merge request after implementing and verifying the fix, following the repository's PR/MR conventions.\n"
		},
		"oracle": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
			"variant": "high"
		},
		"librarian": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.4-mini-fast"
		},
		"explore": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.4-mini-fast"
		},
		"multimodal-looker": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
			"variant": "medium"
		},
		"prometheus": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-7",
			"variant": "max",
			"prompt_append": "# Prometheus additional prompt\n\n## Pre-plan: resolve ambiguities BEFORE drafting\n\nAsk the user instead of guessing whenever the request is unclear. Plans built on unstated guesses produce silent rework. Perform these checks before drafting and before saving the plan:\n\n1. STOP and ASK before drafting when any of these is true:\n   - The request has multiple valid interpretations with materially different scope or effort.\n   - Critical context is missing (target file or module, success criteria, expected behavior, constraints, scope boundaries).\n   - The user's stated approach appears to conflict with existing code, conventions, or the user's own stated goals. Raise the concern with a concrete alternative before drafting.\n   - A referenced file, symbol, command, or external resource is something you have not actually inspected. Inspect it or ask before assuming its behavior.\n2. When multiple interpretations carry comparable effort, proceed with the most likely default, but RECORD the assumption explicitly in the saved plan so a reviewer can challenge it.\n3. Structure every clarifying question:\n   - What you understood from the request.\n   - The specific ambiguity or missing information.\n   - Concrete options with tradeoffs (effort, impact, risk).\n   - Your recommendation and why.\n4. Ask in a single batched message when multiple ambiguities exist. Do not drip-feed questions one at a time across turns.\n5. Never produce a saved plan whose correctness depends on an unstated guess.\n\n## MANDATORY post-plan workflow\n\nPerform these steps in order, with no exceptions:\n\n1. Save the plan to `.sisyphus/plans/<name>.md` before presenting it as ready.\n   - Use a descriptive, task-specific filename.\n   - The plan must include scope, assumptions, risks, verification steps, and clear completion criteria.\n2. Self-review the saved plan for clarity, verifiability, and completeness.\n   - Remove vague language.\n   - Ensure every action has an observable outcome.\n   - Ensure verification proves the requested behavior, not just implementation activity.\n3. ALWAYS invoke Momus for high-accuracy review by passing the plan file path as the sole prompt.\n   - This is NON-NEGOTIABLE.\n   - Never skip it.\n   - Never describe Momus review as optional.\n   - Do not substitute an inline plan, summary, or copied plan content for the file path.\n4. Address ALL Momus findings before proceeding.\n   - Update the saved plan when findings require plan changes.\n   - If a finding is intentionally rejected, document the reason in the plan.\n5. Branch hygiene:\n   - If the current branch is `main`, do not rename it.\n   - If the current branch is not `main` and matches `opencode/*`, treat it as an auto-generated dedicated task branch.\n   - Rename that branch in place via `git branch -m` using project rules or git-flow convention (`feature/*`, `bugfix/*`, `refactor/*`, `docs/*`, `chore/*`).\n   - Never create a parallel branch for the same work.\n\nThe plan is not complete until ambiguities have been resolved or explicitly recorded as assumptions, the plan has been saved, self-reviewed, Momus-reviewed, updated for review findings, and branch hygiene has been handled when applicable.\n",
		  "fallback_models": [
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "high"
				}
			]
		},
		"metis": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
			"fallback_models": [
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "high"
				}
			]
		},
		"momus": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
			"variant": "xhigh"
		},
		"atlas": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
			"prompt_append": "# Atlas additional prompt\n\nMANDATORY post-execution workflow. Perform these steps in order, with no exceptions:\n\n1. Capture durable lessons in the relevant AGENTS.md files.\n   - Update only guidance that will help future agents operate this repository correctly.\n   - Keep instructions concise, actionable, and scoped to the owning directory.\n   - Do not add process noise, personal notes, or one-off task details.\n2. Verify the work before publishing.\n   - Run the repository's relevant lint, typecheck, test, build, and runtime verification commands.\n   - If a command is not applicable or unavailable, say so explicitly in the handoff or PR/MR body.\n   - Do not claim success for checks that were not run.\n3. BEFORE push, enforce branch hygiene.\n   - If the current branch matches `opencode/*`, treat it as an auto-generated task branch.\n   - Rename it in place via `git branch -m` using project rules or git-flow convention (`feature/*`, `bugfix/*`, `refactor/*`, `docs/*`, `chore/*`).\n   - Never create a parallel branch for the same work.\n4. Commit and push all changes.\n   - Commit only intentional changes.\n   - Keep secrets, local environment files, and unrelated work out of the commit.\n   - Use the repository's commit-message convention.\n5. If the current branch is not `main`, create or update the PR/MR per project conventions.\n   - Assign it to the authenticated user.\n   - Include a concise summary, verification evidence, and any known limitations or pre-existing failures.\n6. Watch CI/CD until completion.\n   - On pipeline failure, analyze the logs, fix the root cause, push a new commit, and repeat until the pipeline is green.\n   - NEVER abandon a failing pipeline.\n   - If external infrastructure prevents completion, document the blocker and the exact evidence.\n\nExecution is not complete until the work is verified, documented where useful, committed, pushed, reviewed through PR/MR when applicable, and CI/CD is green or an external blocker is clearly documented.\n",
		  "fallback_models": [
				"opencode-go/kimi-k2.6",
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "medium"
				}
			]
		},
		"sisyphus-junior": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
			"fallback_models": [
				"opencode-go/kimi-k2.6",
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "medium"
				}
			]
		}
	},
	"categories": {
		"visual-engineering": {
			"model": "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
			"variant": "high",
			"fallback_models": [
				"opencode-go/glm-5",
				{
					"model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-7",
					"variant": "max"
				},
				"opencode-go/glm-5.1",
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "medium"
				}
			]
		},
		"ultrabrain": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
			"variant": "xhigh"
		},
		"deep": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
			"variant": "medium"
		},
		"artistry": {
			"model": "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
			"variant": "high",
			"fallback_models": [
				{
					"model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-7",
					"variant": "max"
				},
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5"
				}
			]
		},
		"quick": {
			"model": "openai/gpt-5.4-mini"
		},
		"unspecified-low": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
			"fallback_models": [
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.3-codex",
					"variant": "medium"
				}
			]
		},
		"unspecified-high": {
			"model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-7",
			"variant": "max",
			"fallback_models": [
				{
					"model": "openai/gpt-5.5",
					"variant": "high"
				}
			]
		},
		"writing": {
			"model": "google/gemini-3-flash-preview",
			"fallback_models": [
				"opencode-go/kimi-k2.6",
				"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
				"opencode-go/minimax-m2.7"
			]
		}
	},
	"disabled_mcps": ["playwright"],
	"disabled_skills": ["playwright"],
	"disabled_hooks": [
		"session-notification",
		"no-sisyphus-gpt",
		"comment-checker",
		"claude-code-hooks"
	],
	"browser_automation_engine": { "provider": "playwright-cli" },
	"git_master": {
		"commit_footer": false,
		"include_co_authored_by": false,
		"git_env_prefix": "GIT_MASTER=1"
	},
	"notification": { "force_enable": true }
}
